<PageLayout title="Our History">
  <div class="prose-bfs">
    <p>
      'Bright Futures' began as a small charity in 2007. It was created by a group of parents who were seeking improvements to the quality and range of services for children with autism.
    </p>
    <p>
      In March 2010 Bright Futures secured a 'start-up' grant with which to develop 'special school' provision in partnership with Saddleworth Preparatory School, but when that school closed a few weeks later it became necessary to start from scratch.
    </p>
    <p>
      We were fortunate, in August 2010, to find premises in Grasscroft. In March 2011, the new school underwent a successful 'material change' Ofsted inspection with the outcome that Bright Futures School was registered with the DfE as a special school for children with autism.
    </p>
    <p>
      In February 2020 we moved into our current school building, on Friezland Lane in Greenfield — a purpose-built facility financed by local company Robert Scott and Son, giving every pupil their own 1-1 space.
    </p>

    <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-brand-cyan pl-6 my-8 italic text-gray-600">
      <p>"I was excluded a lot at my other school... I've never been excluded at Bright Futures and for the first time, I feel happy at school."</p>
      <cite class="not-italic text-sm font-semibold text-brand-navy block mt-2">— Bright Futures pupil</cite>
    </blockquote>

    <h2>School Newsletters</h2>
    <p>Our newsletters are shared with parents and carers each term. Please contact the school office for copies.</p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
